==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German [[sal]], from Germanic ''*salaz''.  Cognate with Dutch [[zaal]], Swedish [[sal#Swedish|sal]], Old English [[sele#Old English|sele]].

===Noun===
'''Saal''' ''m'' (plural [[Säle]])
# [[hall]] or large [[room]].

